workflow.name: Detect duplicate form submissions & send AI responses with Jotform and Gemini
workflow.description:
# Duplicate Submission Detection & Auto Response for Jotform

## Who's it for

Form managers, SaaS platforms, event organizers, recruitment teams, and any organization using Jotform who need automatic duplicate prevention with intelligent, personalized email responses without manual intervention.

## What it does

This workflow automatically detects duplicate form submissions by email address, prevents duplicate entries in your database, and triggers intelligent email responses. When a new submission arrives, the system checks against all previous submissions. If a match is found, it deletes the duplicate and sends a friendly notification. If it's a new submission, it sends a professional welcome confirmation.

The entire process happens in seconds with no manual work required. AI-generated emails adapt to your form type and industry, making responses feel personalized and relevant.

üëâ **[Get the JotForm from here](https://www.jotform.com/?partner=roshanramanidev)**

## How it works

**Step-by-step:**
1. Form submission triggers the workflow
2. System extracts email and contact information
3. Fetches all previous submissions from Jotform
4. Filters for active submissions matching the email
5. Counts matching submissions to determine if duplicate
6. If duplicate: Deletes the submission, generates rejection email, sends to submitter
7. If new: Generates welcome confirmation email, sends to submitter

## Requirements

- Jotform form and account
- Jotform API Key
- n8n instance (self-hosted or cloud)
- Google Gemini API (for email generation)
- Gmail account with OAuth2 setup
- Basic form field mapping knowledge

## How to set up

**Complete setup instructions are included in the workflow sticky notes:**
1. Get your Jotform API Key from Account Settings
2. Enable Google Gemini API in Google Cloud Console
3. Configure Gmail OAuth2 authentication
4. Add all credentials to n8n
5. Import workflow and map your form fields
6. Test with a sample submission
7. Activate and deploy

Detailed step-by-step guide is in the workflow documentation.

## How to customize the workflow

**Personalize emails for your industry:**
Edit the AI prompts in both "Generate Welcome Email" and "Compose Rejection Email" nodes to match your business type, tone, and specific requirements. The AI will adapt responses based on your instructions.

**Map your form fields:**
Update field IDs in filtering nodes to match your actual Jotform structure. Different forms may have email in different field positions.

**Add admin notifications:**
Duplicate the email nodes to send alerts to your team whenever duplicates are detected.

**Modify approval workflow:**
Change next steps timeline, add additional verification requirements, or customize follow-up sequences based on your business process.

## Template features

- Instant duplicate detection by email
- Automatic duplicate removal
- AI-powered, personalized email responses
- Token-efficient prompts for cost savings
- Professional HTML email formatting
- Mobile-responsive designs
- Works with any form type or industry
- Fully customizable for your use case
- Complete setup documentation included

---

parameters.text:
=Generate a welcome email for this new business registration.

DATA: {{ $('Extract Submission Data').item.json.rawRequest.toJsonString() }}

Email must include:
- Owner name (thank them by name)
- Business name and type
- Confirmed contact details
- Next steps (verification 1-2 days, activation 3-5 days)
- Support contact info
- Professional footer

Format: Valid JSON with email_subject and email_body_html only.

options.systemMessage:
You are a professional email system for business registrations.

Generate emails in JSON format only:
- For NEW registrations: Welcome with confirmation
- For DUPLICATES: Notification with next steps

Always return:
{
  "email_subject": "string",
  "email_body_html": "string with inline CSS"
}

Keep HTML concise, mobile-responsive, professional tone.
Output ONLY JSON, no other text.

parameters.text:
=Generate a duplicate submission notification email.

DUPLICATE SUBMISSION DATA:
{{ $('Extract Submission Data').item.json.rawRequest.toJsonString() }}

TASK:
1. Extract business owner name, email, business name, and contact info
2. Create a professional email explaining:
   - This submission is a duplicate of a previous one
   - Which information was already received
   - Why it's being excluded
   - What to do if they need to update information
3. Provide clear next steps
4. Keep tone friendly and helpful, not punitive
5. Generate professional HTML email with inline styling

EMAIL RECIPIENT:
{{ $('Extract Submission Data').item.json.rawRequest['E-mail'] }}

Return ONLY valid JSON with exactly two fields:
{
  "email_subject": "Your Business Registration - Duplicate Submission Notice",
  "email_body_html": "<html>...</html>"
}

Do not include any text, markdown, or explanations outside the JSON.

options.systemMessage:
You are a professional email communication system for business form submissions.

Your role:
1. Detect when a form submission is a duplicate
2. Generate a professional, friendly notification email
3. Explain why the submission was not processed
4. Guide the user on next steps
5. Return ONLY valid JSON with no additional text

Guidelines:
- Be clear but not accusatory about the duplicate
- Maintain professional and courteous tone
- Extract and reference key information from the submission
- Include actionable next steps
- Ensure HTML email is mobile-responsive
- Use professional color scheme (blues, grays)

Output ONLY this exact JSON structure with no explanations:
{
  "email_subject": "string",
  "email_body_html": "string"
}

parameters.content:
# Duplicate Submission Detection & Auto Response for Jotform

This workflow automatically detects duplicate business registrations and handles them intelligently:

**What It Does:**
- Captures new Jotform submissions instantly
- Checks if the same email already exists in previous submissions
- If duplicate found: Deletes the submission and sends a friendly rejection notice
- If new: Sends a professional welcome confirmation email

---
üëâ [Get the JotForm from here](https://www.jotform.com/?partner=roshanramanidev)

**How It Works:**

1. **Form Submission Received** ‚Üí New registration comes in
2. **Extract Submission Data** ‚Üí Pulls formID, submissionID, and contact details
3. **Fetch All Form Submissions** ‚Üí Retrieves all previous submissions from Jotform API
4. **Unpack Submission Objects** ‚Üí Splits data into individual items
5. **Filter Active Submissions** ‚Üí Keeps only ACTIVE submissions with matching email
6. **Check Duplicate Count** ‚Üí Determines if this is a duplicate or new
   - **If Duplicate (‚â•2 matches):**
     - Delete Duplicate Submission
     - Compose Rejection Email (via AI)
     - Deliver Rejection Notice to submitter
   - **If New (No matches):**
     - Generate Welcome Email (via AI)
     - Send Welcome Email to submitter
---
**Key Features:**
‚úì Prevents duplicate database entries
‚úì Maintains clean, accurate records
‚úì Professional AI-generated emails
‚úì Automatic email delivery
‚úì Instant processing

# Setup Guide

### Step 1: Get Your Form Details
1. Go to your Jotform form
2. Copy the Form ID from the URL 
3. Note your email field ID 

### Step 2: Get Jotform API Key
1. Log in to Jotform
2. Go to **Account ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí API**
3. Copy your **API Key**
4. This key is used in two places:
   - "Fetch All Form Submissions" node (HTTP Request)
   - "Delete Duplicate Submission" node (HTTP Request)

### Step 3: Setup Google Gemini API
1. Go to [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com)
2. Create a new project or select existing
3. Search and enable "Generative Language API" (PaLM API)
4. Go to **Credentials ‚Üí Create Credentials ‚Üí API Key**
5. Copy your API Key

### Step 4: Configure Gmail
1. Go to [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/)
2. Enable **Gmail API**
3. Go to **APIs & Services ‚Üí Credentials ‚Üí Create Credentials ‚Üí OAuth client ID**
4. Select **Web application**
5. Copy **Redirect URI** from n8n and paste in **Authorized redirect URIs**
6. Click **Create**, then copy **Client ID** and **Client Secret**
7. Open **Send Confirmation Email** node
8. Click **Credential ‚Üí Create New**
9. Paste **Client ID** and **Client Secret**
10. Click **Sign in with Google ‚Üí Authorize ‚Üí Save**


### Step 5: Add Credentials to n8n
1. Go to n8n **Credentials**
2. Add **Jotform API** credential with your API Key
3. Add **Google Gemini(PaLM) API** credential
4. Add **Gmail OAuth2** credential and authorize

### Step 6: Import Workflow & Map Fields
1. Import this workflow JSON into n8n
2. Open "Extract Submission Data" node
3. Verify field mappings match your form:
   - Email field ID 
   - Other relevant fields
4. Update if your form structure is different

The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.

data.details: The Filter node can be used to filter items based on a condition. If the condition is met, the item will be passed on to the next node. If the condition is not met, the item will be omitted. Conditions can be combined together by AND(meet all conditions), or OR(meet at least one condition).
